cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.SE 

This paper deals with reasoning about concurrent programs and their semantics, specifically under the Total Store Ordering (TSO) memory model. This falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO) categories. The paper also discusses reduction theory, which is a technique used in distributed computing (cs.DC) and abstraction mechanisms, which are commonly used in software engineering (cs.SE) and computer architecture (cs.AR). Therefore, these categories are also likely candidates.
